@L1F3cycle
Search the net for a program called Fast AVI MPEG Splitter. It does the trick and it's easy to use.

And as for the subtitle thingy, download a software called Subtitle Workshop. When installed and opened go to Tools - Join Subtitles. Put the cd1 first then cd2. Click on the Set Movie Fragment, find the newly created .avi and click ok and then join...Save the newly created file as .srt and you are set to go.
